.TH BLK-ARCHIVE 1 "July 2025" "blk-archive" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
blk-archive - deduplicated archiving for block devices and files

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B blk-archive
[OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B blk-archive
is a tool for archiving block devices and individual files. It works especially well with thin provisioned device-mapper targets. It supports deduplication, delta compression, and efficient unpacking.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -j, --json
Output in JSON format.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Display help information.
.TP
.B -V, --version
Show version information.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B create
Create a new archive.
.RS
.B Usage:
blk-archive create [OPTIONS] --archive 
.PP
Options:
.TP
\fB-a, --archive \fR
Specify archive directory.
.TP
\fB-j, --json\fR
Output JSON.
.TP
\fB--block-size <BLOCK_SIZE>\fR
Specify average block size for deduplication.
.TP
\fB--hash-cache-size-meg <HASH_CACHE_SIZE_MEG>\fR
Memory for caching hash entries.
.TP
\fB--data-cache-size-meg <DATA_CACHE_SIZE_MEG>\fR
Memory for caching data.
.TP
\fB--data-compression <y|n>\fR
Enable/disable slab data compression. Default: y.
.RE

.TP
.B pack
Pack a stream into the archive.
.RS
.B Usage:
blk-archive pack [OPTIONS] --archive  
.PP
Arguments:
.TP
\fB\fR
Device or file to archive.
.PP
Options:
.TP
\fB-a, --archive \fR
Specify archive directory. [env: BLK_ARCHIVE_DIR=]
.TP
\fB-j, --json\fR
Output JSON.
.TP
\fB--delta-stream <DELTA_STREAM>\fR
Use a stream with an older version for delta compression.
.TP
\fB--delta-device <DELTA_DEVICE>\fR
Use a device with an older version for delta compression.
.TP
\fB--data-cache-size-meg \fR
Cache size for data.
.RE

.TP
.B unpack
Unpack a stream from the archive.
.RS
.B Usage:
blk-archive unpack [OPTIONS] --archive  --stream  
.PP
Arguments:
.TP
\fB\fR
Destination device or file.
.PP
Options:
.TP
\fB--create\fR
Create a new file instead of overwriting.
.TP
\fB-j, --json\fR
Output JSON.
.TP
\fB--data-cache-size-meg \fR
Cache size for data.
.TP
\fB-a, --archive \fR
Specify archive directory. [env: BLK_ARCHIVE_DIR=]
.TP
\fB-s, --stream \fR
Stream to unpack.
.RE

.TP
.B verify
Verify archived stream against a device/file.
.RS
.B Usage:
blk-archive verify [OPTIONS] --archive  --stream  
.PP
Arguments:
.TP
\fB\fR
Device or file with the correct data.
.PP
Options:
.TP
\fB--data-cache-size-meg \fR
Cache size for data.
.TP
\fB-j, --json\fR
Output JSON.
.TP
\fB-a, --archive \fR
Specify archive directory. [env: BLK_ARCHIVE_DIR=]
.TP
\fB-s, --stream \fR
Stream to verify.
.RE

.TP
.B dump-stream
Development tool: inspect stream instructions.
.RS
.B Usage:
blk-archive dump-stream [OPTIONS] --archive  --stream 
.PP
Options:
.TP
\fB-a, --archive \fR
Specify archive directory.
.TP
\fB-j, --json\fR
Output JSON.
.TP
\fB-s, --stream \fR
Stream to inspect.
.RE

.TP
.B list
List streams in an archive.
.RS
.B Usage:
blk-archive list [OPTIONS] --archive 
.PP
Options:
.TP
\fB-a, --archive \fR
Specify archive directory.
.TP
\fB-j, --json\fR
Output JSON.
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBBLK_ARCHIVE_DIR\fR
Used as the default archive directory if --archive is not specified.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a new archive:
blk-archive create --archive /archives/my-archive
.TP
Pack a device:
blk-archive pack --archive /archives/my-archive /dev/sdx
.TP
Unpack a stream to a file:
blk-archive unpack --archive /archives/my-archive --stream 001 out.img
.TP
Verify data integrity:
blk-archive verify --archive /archives/my-archive --stream 001 /dev/sdx

.SH AUTHOR
Joe Thornber

